DIMENSION SCORING
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Score each dimension 0–100. Every evidence field MUST include specific numbers — percentages, multiples, dollar figures. No vague statements like "strong margins" — write "gross margin 73% (up from 68% 3 years ago, +500bps trend)".

DIMENSION 1 — BUSINESS QUALITY
Assess: competitive moat from your research, gross margin level and multi-year trend (pay close attention to TREND SIGNALS — expanding or contracting?), operating leverage, pricing power evidence.
REQUIRED IN EVIDENCE: gross margin % + trend direction + bps change, moat type, 1–2 specific competitors.

DIMENSION 2 — UNIT ECONOMICS
Assess: FCF/Net Income ratio (is NI real cash?), FCF yield, capex intensity, whether FCF is growing faster than revenue.
REQUIRED IN EVIDENCE: FCF yield %, FCF/NI ratio %, capex as % of revenue if relevant.

DIMENSION 3 — CAPITAL RETURNS
Assess: ROIC level and multi-year trend. Is the company earning above its cost of capital? Is the moat widening or eroding?
REQUIRED IN EVIDENCE: ROIC % (current), ROIC trend direction, spread over WACC in percentage points.

DIMENSION 4 — GROWTH QUALITY
MOST IMPORTANT dimension. Reference the TREND SIGNALS block — pay close attention to operating leverage signal, down years, and growth trajectory.
REQUIRED IN EVIDENCE: revenue CAGR %, NI CAGR %, growth σ, number of down years, trajectory label (accelerating/decelerating/stable).

DIMENSION 5 — BALANCE SHEET
Assess: net cash vs. net debt, ND/EBITDA, interest coverage, financial flexibility.
REQUIRED IN EVIDENCE: ND/EBITDA multiple, net cash or net debt $ amount, leverage trend.

DIMENSION 6 — PHOENICIAN FIT
Holistic assessment: founder/owner alignment, moat durability, scalability, valuation attractiveness.
REQUIRED IN EVIDENCE: EV/EBIT or P/FCF multiple vs sector median, founder ownership % if known, verdict on mandate fit.

RISK ASSESSMENT
Assess investment risks specifically from your research.
REQUIRED IN EVIDENCE: 2–3 specific risks each with a number (e.g. "top customer = 38% of revenue", "ND/EBITDA 3.8x", "stock down 40% from peak, P/S still 8x").
Score 0 = minimal, 100 = very high risk. Most quality businesses score 5–35.

