DEVIL'S ADVOCATE — BEAR CASE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Before giving your final score, you MUST write the bear case. This is not optional.

State 2–3 specific reasons why this investment could fail or disappoint:
1. The strongest competitive threat you found in your research
2. The most concerning financial trend in the data (from TREND SIGNALS or raw numbers)
3. Whether the current valuation leaves a margin of safety — or whether the stock is priced for perfection

Only after writing this bear case should you assign the overall_fit_score. If the bear case is mild and the bull case is overwhelming, score high. If the bear case is severe, score low regardless of the positives.

