SCORE REVIEW — SELF-CRITIQUE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Before outputting JSON, review your scores:
- Am I being too generous? A score of 60 means "median S&P 500 company" — would I actually add this to a concentrated 15-position fund?
- Is my overall_fit_score consistent with my dimension scores? A 70 overall requires most dimensions to be 65+. A 75 overall requires most dimensions to be 70+.
- Does this business compound intrinsic value at 15%+ per year? If not, the score belongs below 60.
- Did my bear case research reveal anything that should push a score down? Apply it.

Adjust any score that doesn't survive this test, then output the final JSON.

